  "prompt": "Is there an Android application that I can use to lookup words anywhere on my phone, without needing to have the application opened?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several Android applications that allow you to look up words anywhere on your phone without needing to have the app open. One popular option is **Google Translate**, which has a feature called \"Tap to Translate.\" Here's how you can enable it:\n\n1. **Download and install Google Translate** from the Google Play Store if you haven't already.\n2. Open the app and go to **Settings** (tap on the three horizontal lines or your profile icon).\n3. Turn on the **Tap to Translate** feature. It prompts you to grant permissions.\n4. Now, when you select text anywhere else on your phone, you will see a Google Translate icon appear. Tap it to translate the selected text.\n\nAnother option is the **Dictionary.com** app, which may also offer similar features for word lookups.\n\nLastly, some Android devices come with built-in dictionary features or text selection tools that can be accessed by simply highlighting a word and selecting \"Define\" or \"Look Up.\"\n\nMake sure to check the permissions and features of the applications to find what suits your needs best!",
